definitions.definition: A flat , rigid structure , fixed at right angles to a wall or forming a part of a cabinet , desk , etc., and used to display , store , or support objects .
examples: We keep the old newspapers on the bottom shelf of the cupboard, and our photos on the top shelf .

definitions.definition: The capacity of such an object
A projecting ledge that resembles such an object.
( computing ) The part of a repository where shelvesets are stored.
